4 PART III. VARIOUS CONTRACTOR BOARDS
5
6 INCREASE CERTAIN PLUMBING AND HEATING BOARD CONTRACTOR BOARD
7 EXAMINATION AND LICENSE FEES
8 SECTION 3.1.(a) G.S. 87-22 reads as rewritten:
9 "§ 87-22. License fee; expiration and renewal; reinstatement.
10 All persons, firms, or corporations engaged in the business of either plumbing or heating
11 contracting, or both, shall pay an annual license fee not to exceed one hundred fifty dollars
12 ($150.00). three hundred dollars ($300.00). The annual fee for a piping or restricted classification
13 license shall not exceed that for a plumbing or heating license. All persons, firms, or corporations
14 engaged in the business of fire sprinkler contracting shall pay an initial application fee not to
15 exceed seventy-five dollars ($75.00) and an annual license fee not to exceed three hundred dollars
16 ($300.00). In the event the Board refuses to license an applicant, the license fee deposited shall
17 be returned by the Board to the applicant. All licenses shall expire on the last day of December
18 in each year following their issuance or renewal. Persons who obtain a license by passing an
19 examination on or after October 1 of any year may receive a license for the remainder of the year
20 by paying one-half of the usual license fee for that classification of license. It shall be the duty
21 of the secretary and treasurer to send by United States mail or e-mail to every licensee registered
22 with the Board, notice to the licensee's last known address reflected on the records of the Board
23 of the amount of fee required for renewal of license, the notice to be mailed at least one month
24 in advance of the expiration of the license. The Board may require payment of all unpaid annual
25 fees before reissuing a license. In the event of failure on the part of any person, firm or
26 corporation to renew the license certificate annually and pay the required fee during the month
27 of January in each year, the Board shall increase the license fee by twenty-five dollars ($25.00)
28 an amount not to exceed fifty dollars ($50.00) to cover any additional expense associated with
29 late renewal. The Board shall require reexamination upon failure of a licensee to renew license
30 within three years after expiration. The Board may adopt regulations requiring attendance at
31 programs of continuing education as a condition of license renewal. A licensee employed full
32 time as a local government plumbing, heating, or mechanical inspector and holding qualifications
33 from the Code Officials Qualifications Board may renew the license at a fee not to exceed
34 twenty-five dollars ($25.00)."
35 SECTION 3.1.(b) G.S. 87-22.1 reads as rewritten:
36 "§ 87-22.1. Examination fees; funds disbursed upon warrant of chairman and
37 secretary-treasurer.
38 The Board shall charge a nonrefundable application and examination fee not to exceed one
39 hundred fifty dollars ($150.00) two hundred dollars ($200.00) for each examination or any part
40 of an examination, and the funds collected shall be disbursed upon warrant of the chairman and
41 secretary-treasurer, to partially defray general expenses of the Board. The application and
42 examination fee shall be retained by the Board whether or not the applicant is granted a license.
43 Until changed by the Board pursuant to rules adopted by the Board, the fee for each examination
44 or any part taken on a particular day shall be one hundred dollars ($100.00)."
45 SECTION 3.1.(c) This section becomes effective July 1, 2025, and applies to
46 applications for examination and licensure received by the Board on or after that date.
