7 engineering, and three shall be public members. Of the general contractor members, one shall
8 have as the larger part of his the contractor's business the construction of highways; one shall
9 have as the larger part of his the contractor's business the construction of public utilities; one
10 shall have as the larger part of his the contractor's business the construction of buildings; and two
11 shall have as a larger part of their the contractor's businesses the construction of residences, one
12 of whom shall be the holder of an unlimited general contractor's license. The public members
13 shall have no ties with the construction industry and shall represent the interests of the public at
14 large. Members shall serve until the expiration of their respective terms and until their successors
15 are appointed and qualified. Vacancies occurring during a term shall be filled by appointment of
16 the Governor for the remainder of the unexpired term. The Governor may remove any member
17 of the Board for misconduct, incompetency, or neglect of duty. No Board member shall serve
18 more than two complete consecutive terms.
