9 "§ 143-151.12. Powers.
10 In addition to powers conferred upon the Board elsewhere in this Article, the Board has the
11 power to do the following:
12 (1) Adopt rules necessary to administer this Article.
13 (1a) Require State agencies, local inspection departments, and local governing
14 bodies to submit reports and information about the employment, education,
15 and training of Code-enforcement officials.
16 (2) Establish minimum standards for employment as a Code-enforcement official:
17 (i) in probationary or temporary status, and (ii) in permanent positions.
18 (3) Certify persons as being qualified under the provisions of this Article to be
19 Code-enforcement officials, including persons employed by a federally
20 recognized Indian Tribe to perform inspections on tribal lands.
21 (3a) Certify persons as being qualified under the provisions of this Article to be
22 North Carolina State Building Code Permit Technicians.
23 (3b) Certify persons as being qualified under the provisions of this Article to be
24 residential changeout special inspectors.
