46 complete such in-service training as may be prescribed by the Board. At the earliest practicable
47 date, such official shall receive from the Board a limited certificate qualifying him to engage in
48 Code enforcement at the level, in the particular type of position, and within the governmental
49 jurisdiction in which he the Code-enforcement official is employed. The limited certificate shall
50 be valid only as an authorization for the Code-enforcement official to continue in the position he
51 held on the applicable date and shall become invalid if he the Code-enforcement official does not
