32 "§ 143-151.23. Disasters and emergencies; temporary certificates.
33 (a) When a state of emergency, as defined in G.S. 166A-19.3, has been declared by the
34 Governor due to a natural disaster such as a hurricane, tornado, or flood, or due to a pending
35 disaster, the Board may issue temporary standard or limited certificates to retired qualified
36 Code-enforcement officials to conduct Code enforcement in the emergency area, as defined in
37 G.S. 166A-19.3, for the duration of the state of emergency.
38 (b) A temporary standard or limited certificate issued under this section shall expire at
39 the termination of the state of emergency or 12 months, whichever is earlier. If after 12 months
40 the state of emergency has not expired, the Board may renew the temporary standard or limited
41 certificate.
42 (c) A qualified Code-enforcement official who has been on inactive status and is issued
43 a temporary standard or limited certificate under this section shall not be subject to the continuing
44 education requirements established pursuant to G.S. 143-151.13A, unless the individual has been
45 inactive or retired for over two years and not continuously employed by a city or county
46 inspection department.
