1 (d) For the purposes of this section, the phrase "residential changeout" means work
2 requiring a building permit for the purpose of heating and air conditioning appliance and water
3 heater replacement in dwellings subject to the North Carolina Residential Code, and individual
4 residential units of condominiums and apartments provided the individual appliance serves only
5 that residential dwelling unit."
6 SECTION 4.1.(c) By July 1, 2025, the Office of the State Fire Marshal shall develop
7 an internet-based examination and short course as described in G.S. 143-151.24, as enacted by
8 subsection (a) of this section, and make it available on the Office's website for the purpose of
